This paper deals with routing in computer networks, which is a topic related to computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of algorithms to optimize routing decisions, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of a multi-armed bandit framework is a machine learning technique, which is related to the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the issue of adversarial attacks, which is related to the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
